# The .gcloudignore file excludes file from upload to Cloud Build.
# If this file is deleted, gcloud will default to .gitignore.
#
# https://cloud.google.com/cloud-build/docs/speeding-up-builds#gcloudignore
# https://cloud.google.com/sdk/gcloud/reference/topic/gcloudignore

.git/
.github/
.vercel/
.vscode/

# Dependencies and build outputs are (re)produced inside the Docker builder.
**/node_modules/
**/out/
**/dist/
**/.dev/

# Legacy / experimental — NOT npm-workspace members, so safe to keep out of the
# upload. A manual `gcloud builds submit` runs `npm ci`, which needs every
# workspace member present; these are excluded from the root workspaces array
# (concept-generator via the `!packages/concept-generator` negation), so they
# must NOT be workspace members or this would break the install.
admin/
impower-app/
vscode-spark/
packages/concept-generator/

.gitignore
README.md
